Title: Narrow pod informer cache to operator-managed pods only

Description:

Currently the controller watches Pods cluster-wide. A predicate (rootenv.io/managed-by: labenv-operator) filters out foreign pods, so Reconcile only fires for our pods — reconcile-level work is already efficient. However, the underlying informer still receives, caches, and streams all pods in the cluster from the api-server; the predicate filters in-memory, after the network/cache hop.

This is negligible for MVP and small/medium clusters, but on large clusters (tens of thousands of pods) the informer wastes network traffic and memory caching pods we never act on.

Fix: add a label-scoped cache in main.go so the informer only watches pods carrying our label, filtering at the api-server level instead of in-memory:
go

Cache: cache.Options{
    ByObject: map[client.Object]cache.ByObject{
        &corev1.Pod{}: {
            Label: labels.SelectorFromSet(labels.Set{"rootenv.io/managed-by": "labenv-operator"}),
        },
    },
},

Priority: low — optimization, not correctness. Revisit when cluster pod count grows or memory footprint matters.